id: pm-3rjo
title: Compact strict-create recovery duplicates missing fields under two keys
description: "9379cefa (compact strict create recovery) sets both 'missing' and 'missing_required_fields' to the same combinedMissingFlags array in src/cli/commands/create.ts:1541-1545, and renderRecoveryBundle (src/cli/error-guidance.ts) prints BOTH lines, so the compact recovery bundle - whose purpose is token efficiency - emits the identical flag list twice. Repro: in a strict-mode workspace run pm create with a type missing required fields; recovery bundle shows 'missing: --x' and 'missing_required_fields: --x'. Fix options: emit only missing_required_fields in compact mode (drop the legacy 'missing' alias there), or have renderRecoveryBundle suppress missing when missing_required_fields is identical. Also minor: suggested_flags mixes a flag+value token ('--create-mode progressive') with bare flags."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[3]: agent-ux,audit-2026-06-12,token-efficiency
created_at: "2026-06-12T16:11:27.751Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-12T16:56:19.344Z"
author: maintainer-agent
resolution: Removed duplicate missing alias from compact strict-create recovery payloads.
expected_result: Compact recovery emits missing_required_fields once without duplicating the same data under missing.
actual_result: Governance preset regression test and manual strict-create temp workflow confirmed missing is absent and missing_required_fields remains present.
